    "asOf": "2021-04-28",
    "date": "2021-10-05T13:57:33Z",
    "text": "Modernizing Seat Back Safety Act \n\nThis bill requires the Department of Transportation (DOT) to issue a final rule revising motor vehicle seating systems safety standards to reduce the potential for injury to all motor vehicle occupants due to seat back failure during all types of vehicle impact.\n\nDOT must also establish a date for required compliance with the final rule of not later than two motor vehicle model years after the model year during which the effective date of the final rule occurs."
  },
